Never checked on drinks or how our food was. I had Blackened tacos, which were ice cold, Blackened Mahi Tacos were fishy and cold as well. Burritos that were ordered were tasty, but luke warm. I don’t quite know where to start. The first thing was the hockey game that was on TV. It was so loud that we had to actually yell to each other and the server. We asked two people to please turn it down but were pretty much ignored. We ordered drinks which were delivered and the beer was ok but the margarita was very small for the price. The waitress disappeared for a long time and when the food was FINALLY delivered, my husband’s burrito was cold and the other two people who each ordered fajitas received a small platter of one slice of green pepper and one slice of red pepper along with a shrimp and a few pieces of other meat. Disappointing at the least . Oh and when the game was over, they left the volume where it was through commercials and random announcements. I couldn’t wait to get out of there. Wouldn’t go back if you paid me.

Love a good Mexican restaurant especially if they serve good margaritas. Unfortunately, the regular margarita was probably one of the worst I've ever had and, for the size, overpriced.  I switched it out for their strawberry margarita which wasn't great but was an improvement.  Chips and salsa are not automatically served so we ordered the chips and guacamole which was very fresh and delicious.  Had a chicken quesadilla which was pretty good but I think there are better Mexican restaurants in town with more reasonable priced food & drinks.

We had a good experience thanks to Priority Pass (and based on previous reviews, were not expecting to). Early flight meant we came here for breakfast with 2 hours to spare. Just 2 other parties were in the restaurant when we arrived. We told our server (Teresita, who was great! Management, please take note!) that we were using Priority Pass and she swiped our card - no drama there. Our order included breakfast tacos, huevos rancheros, coffee, and a Coke, and came out relatively quickly (i.e., we had plenty of time to get to our gate). We didn't come close to hitting the $28 per person limit, but we DID ask about paying tip with credit card and that is something you can do very easily.

Waitress would disappear for long time. Restaurant half full. I never complain Ever. We are from AZ and i think we are good judges on Mexican food. The wife and I shared the chicken nachos and the chicken  Enchiladas. Both were amazing and the price was not hight for  Vegas standards. And the hot salsa is definitely hot. Well diffenitly go back there. And you can park in there hotel and walk freemont street and the restaurant will validate your parking ticket.  Win win.

Went here on the 29th to watch the 49ers seahawks game with my wife.  Staff was attentive, restaurant was clean and modern.  We had a cool couch and table to hang around which is so much better than a stool to watch a football game,  so we were comfortable. Atmosphere was loud because of the tv but that's expected.  Lots of TVs with several sports on but catering to SNF game.  So far so good......  The food was "Mexican "  by description but not by taste.  I could barely taste the salsa that came with the chips. ($6.00)  I had a combo plate, taco--ground beef it was 'meh'   , a cheese enchilada. Had no distinction as to ingredients, just a hot mass of cheese, and a chicken quesadilla which was ok owing to the cilantro which makes anything taste good.  It was hot,   it looked appetizing but just did not do it for me--a native so cal guy-- on any level.  There ya go, it was convenient and friendly but not very tasty.

We enjoy going out. Yesterday we  found this delicious restaurant which friends told us about. We enjoyed a beautiful time there with great dishes and  an experienced stuff and a distinguished  chef. We put this restaurant in our list  and we will certainly go again soon. We warmly recommend.

We have eaten there twice. First time was great, seated at the bar, our orders taken quickly food out fast bar tender super nice and efficient. Second time was much different... There were tables that sat dirty the whole time we were there, no one ever cleaned them. The food is good but service was definitely lacking.

Located in Carson Tower at the Golden Nugget, Las Vegas, with a great view of the award-winning H2O Pool featuring The Tank. Numerous high definition flat screen TVs adorn the walls of the location, showcasing live games and sporting events throughout the day. Inside the venue, you will see two unique Tequila Towers filled with Mexico's superstar tequila brands providing a perfect backdrop for a photo op. We were in the mood for some margaritas and some good Mexican food while we were enjoying the freak-show that is the Fremont Street Experience so we stopped into the Cadillac Mexican Kitchen.  We started off with some Guacamole and Muy Caliente buffalo wings.  The guac was good, and the wings were HOT!!!!  So hot in fact that they were punishing our chapped lips that were damaged from spending too much time in the sun at Red Rock Canyon earlier that day.  Never fear, for we discovered that it was possible to still enjoy the wings if you simply used your fork to strip off all of the meat and delicately insert it into your mouth without coming into contact with our over-sensitive, sun-damaged lips.  There were plenty of TVs to enjoy various sporting events, and the wait staff was very friendly and attentive.

I had the chance to try this place since I attended the Nevada Coalition Conference 2018; and it’s so gooood!!! The service was quick since it was lunch time and the staff was very friendly.
